    mainHeader: "Celebrating Colours",
    subHeader: "",
    contentHeader: "Celebrating Colours",
    content:
      "<p class='first'><span>Bright and eclectic colours have made a comeback in the fashion industry during the past few years. We see them everywhere, on celebrities, during Fashion Weeks and in the streets. They come in every shape and form, from shoes to shirts, from sunglasses to bags. Either you want to wear it as a </span><em>pop of colour</em><span>, total black outfit with a bright pink bag, </span><em>touch of exaggeration </em><span>or as a </span><em>mix &amp; match </em><span>of beautiful fluorescent colours, (almost) anything goes. </span></p><p><span>A study reported that, in the digital age, the three most attractive colours, in relevance to fashion, out of the Pantone colours are Black, Pink Yarrow and Blazing Yellow (Kodžoman et al., 2022). Contray to previous studies stating the preferred colours were blue and red, and that the least favorite were green and yellow.<div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-2 '><div class='w-[200px]  m-auto sm:w-auto sm:h-[600px]'><img src='/images/celebrating-colours-2.jpg' class='object-cover h-full ' /></div><div class='w-[200px] m-auto  sm:w-auto sm:h-[600px]'><img src='/images/celebrating-colours-3.jpg' class=' object-cover h-full ' /></div></div> </span></p><p><span>Apart from the astonishing combinations, bright colours have also been proven to have a positive impact on mental health. In fact, black outfits are commonly associated with a sad feeling, whereas colorful ones are linked to happier feelings. Orange makes you feel energized and enthusiastic. Red makes you feel passionate. Yellow makes you feel happy and spontaneous. Green makes you feel optimistic and refreshed. Blue makes you feel safe and relaxed. Purple makes you feel creative. Pink makes you feel playful and romantic. Black feels sophisticated, classic and serious. White means minimalism and simplicity and Gray feels professional. However, it is worth mentioning that color associations are subjective and can vary from person to person depending on life experiences. </span></p><p><span>Finally, colours in fashion can be an new exciting way of choosing and defining your personality each day, allowing you to make a bold and loud statement. </span></p>",
